                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13777943" author="lexlythius" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 19:11:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This happens only when querying for some particular values on a secondary index. Cannot reproduce it querying by primary key.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Neither of the following did any good:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Restarting Cassandra
nodetool rebuild_index DB TABLE INDEX
nodetool invalidaterowcache
nodetool invalidatekeycache
nodetool cleanup
nodetool repair
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777971" author="lexlythius" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 19:25:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dropping the secondary index and creating it again solved the problem at hand.&lt;br/&gt;
I still think the issue is worth looking into, though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13778697" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 26 Sep 2013 12:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right, that&apos;s a legit issue. Attaching simple patch to fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13778765" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 26 Sep 2013 13:27:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good, can you add a unit test?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13782101" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 30 Sep 2013 18:53:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update patch with some unit testing inside.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13782120" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 30 Sep 2013 19:22:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
